This example demonstrates how to use the BornAgain core C++ API.

GISAS from mixture of uncorrelated cylinders and prisms is simulated,
and the result is plotted using CERN Root.

THIS C++ EXAMPLE IS CURRENTLY NOT MAINTAINED AND MAY BE OUT OF PHASE.

How to compile and run the example.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.1) Install third party software
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Required:
* compilers: as for compiling BornAgain
* cmake, boost, Eigen3: as for BornAgain
* ROOT framework (to plot the result)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.2) Setup BornAgain library
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* install BornAgain library
* add BornAgain libraries to path by running: source <BornAgain_install_dir>/bin/thisbornagain.sh

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) Build given example with CMake
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
mkdir <build_dir>
cd <build_dir>
cmake <this_source_dir>
make

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) Running the simulation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cd <build_dir>
./CylindersAndPrisms
